      Things happen
   =20
 =20
New SEC Boss Wants  More Crypto Oversight to Protect Investors. Global Bank=
s=E2=80=99 $170 Billion Haul Marks  Most Profitable Year Ever. Coal Project=
s in Asia Face Dwindling Financing as Climate Pressure Mounts. Biden Fed Pi=
ck Pits Powell Against Liberal  Push for Regulation. Theranos Patients: The=
 Emerging Wild Card in the Trial of Elizabeth Holmes. Goldman Sachs mints b=
illions through business it is looking to shrink. Tencent Weighs China Game=
s Ban After =E2=80=98 Spiritual Opium=E2=80=99 Rebuke. Cryptocurrency in th=
e infrastructure bill: The industry won last-minute concessions. The sackin=
g of a crypto mecca.=C2=A0Fintechs Need to Be Regulated More Like Banks, Sa=
ys Report From Global Regulator Group.=C2=A0 CFA Level II Success Rate Fall=
s to Lowest Level in a Decade. NYC to Require Restaurant Customers to Show =
 Vaccination Proof. Olympic cameraman stopped filming field hockey to focus=
 on a cockroach in the game's final minutes, baffling fans.=C2=A0If you'd l=
ike to get=C2=A0Money=C2=A0Stuff=C2=A0in handy email form, right in your in=
box, please=C2=A0subscribe at this link. Or you can subscribe to Money Stuf=
f and other great Bloomberg newsletters here. Thanks![1] And so *they* can =
have a pleasant audit experience, of course. Both because it is generally n=
ice for your work to be friendly and non-adversarial, and also because it i=
s easier to do an audit if management trusts you and gives you the informat=
ion you ask for.[2] I am quoting, here and in the rest of this section, fro=
m the two SEC orders, one about Stiehl and the other about EY and its partn=
ers, including Herring. A weird tic of government style is that the Stiehl =
order doesn=E2=80=99t name the EY partners but gives them descriptions like=
 =E2=80=9CAudit Partner=E2=80=9D (for Herring), while the EY order doesn=E2=
=80=99t name Stiehl but calls him =E2=80=9CCAO.=E2=80=9D But you can read b=
oth orders and tell who=E2=80=99s who. I just substitute in the names.[3] S=
ealed Air=E2=80=99s 2015 proxy statement says that Stiehl joined as CAO in =
January 2013. Paragraph 35 of the SEC order against EY quotes a November 20=
14=C2=A0Form 8-K of the issuer; the language matches this Sealed Air 8-K. P=
aragraph 6 of the SEC order against Stiehl notes that he later became actin=
g and then permanent CFO at the issuer, and was terminated=C2=A0in June 201=
9. Here=E2=80=99s Sealed Air=E2=80=99s June 2019 announcement that it fired=
 Stiehl for cause over this investigation.[4] This also seems bad: =E2=80=
=9COn September 15, 2014, EY and three other competing audit firms submitte=
d their initial confidential bid proposals to Issuer. The proposals contain=
ed detailed staffing and billing information, including Excel spreadsheets =
that included hundreds of engagement team names and email addresses, specif=
ic billing rates, budgeted hours, proposed bid amounts, and staffing levels=
 covering dozens of international jurisdictions. [Stiehl]=C2=A0immediately =
forwarded the complete bid proposals provided by two competing audit firms,=
 including all supporting Excel spreadsheets, to Herring. In a footnote bel=
ow its table of contents, the incumbent firm=E2=80=99s bid proposal express=
ly included an =E2=80=9Cirreparable harm=E2=80=9D confidentiality provision=
. On the early morning of September 16, 2014, Herring asked for a copy of t=
he third competing audit firm=E2=80=99s bid proposal, which CAO emailed in =
its entirety to Herring later that same morning.=E2=80=9D You can=E2=80=99t=
 do that! Come on![5] Also sports tickets, always sports tickets. During th=
e RFP process, Stiehl =E2=80=9Cmet Herring for dinner and they, along with =
Fochtmann and others from EY and Issuer attended a National Football League=
 game in EY=E2=80=99s suite in Charlotte, North Carolina.=E2=80=9D[6] Also =
suggesting that Goldman bankers who *do* wear bespoke suits =E2=80=94=C2=A0=
and of course there are many of them, mostly=C2=A0in the senior ranks =E2=
=80=94=C2=A0would be like =E2=80=9Cah, got the memo, guess I=E2=80=99ll wea=
r Dockers to my client meeting=C2=A0tomorrow.=E2=80=9D No.=C2=A0
